<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="deliberately-adv">deliberately <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /dɪ'lɪbərətli/    美 /dɪ'lɪbərətli/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-on-purpose">1.★ <strong>故意地(on purpose)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Not by accident, she deliberately broke that beautiful vase. 
她不是无意，而是故意打破那个漂亮花瓶的。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>慎重地；不慌不忙地：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He packed up his possessions slowly and deliberately.
他慢慢地、小心翼翼地收拾好自己的物品。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Don’t defend him any more. It’s obvious that he <strong><em>_</em></strong>_  (故意地) destroyed the fence of the garden even without apology.   （2013 湖北改）<br />
A.accidentally<br />
B.carelessly<br />
C.deliberately<br />
D.clumsily  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. deliberately  </p></div>